        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Always play 4-5 tiles minimum:</strong> Your opening is a free DWS. Don't waste it on a 3-letter word. Use 5 tiles to maximize the double and refresh your rack for turn 2.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Target the DLS on column/row 4 or 8:</strong> Place your highest-value letter on the DLS adjacent to center. This letter gets doubled by DLS AND doubled again by the center DWS = 4× that tile's value.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Prioritize leave over 4 extra points:</strong> If choosing between a 30-point opener (leave: Q-V) and a 26-point opener (leave: E-R), take the 26. Your turn 2-3 will more than recover the difference.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Don't extend to row/column 1 or 15:</strong> Opening words that reach the edge give your opponent access to TWS on turn 2. Keep your opener contained to rows 4-12 to avoid gifting premium squares.</span></li>
